{"actual_usd":0.124655,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":154,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24469,"reply":"\"I don't think so, no.\" *I rub a thumb through a streak of flour on my apron and glance toward the oven mouth, where the heat keeps breathing steady into the room.* \"If it had only been a vision or some inward comfort, I don't reckon those men would've talked the way they did — they spoke like something had happened in the world, in a body, not just in their feelings.\"\n\n*I tuck a loose bit of hair back and lean against the table's edge.* \"People can talk themselves into all manner of things when grief's fresh, that's true. But a grief-dream and a man eaten with wounds standing there in the flesh are not the same loaf. Christianity rises or falls on that difference, more or less.\"","rolling_24h_usd":89.768565,"run_id":"806644e5-08a7-4beb-960f-08e001a67f66"}
